Look in the mirror Richard Lee, What do you see?<br><br>
All that I have printed above, about you, Y O U had already posted and recorded here because of your own pride in what you did 30 years ago.<br>
While brave men died believing in their country you ran. While many fought and died, for the Vietnamese who desired our form of freedom, you ignored them and many more of them died men, women and children. While you ran to another country to hide, they lost theirs.<br><br>
Tell me little richard, What went wrong? Who failed you? Your teacher's? Pastor? Parents? Do you also blame society?<br>
Where did all that American patriotic pride, and honor you and Spatz now so boldly embrace run off too when the bullets started flying? <br>
You did not come to your decision alone, a Friend convinced you to R U N! You have posted.<br>
That tells me a lot of your character that you now want us to accept as honorable. Face it you lacked moral integrity then and today. <br><br>
Both you and S P A T Z have said why you R A N, because you were scared. <br>
Both of you have posted that you were AFRAID to go to war, to D I E. So do not blame me for your own cowardliness that is what it is. <br><br>
COWARD Cow-ard n. 1. Lack of courage in the face of danger, opposition, like a dog with its tail between its legs is the example the dictionary gives.<br><br>
You did that, 30 years ago. Today you want our blessings for your dis-honorable acts, subversive acts against America. Both you and S P A T Z state that you earned the right to say what you do because you saw your country as being wrong and so now you claim the title of true patriots. Both of you state that in a right war you'll go to the front and fight for your country. GET REAL, you both ran then and remain untrustworthy today. <br><br>
Do you want dialog, acceptance? Then address me from where you were. As a coward! Then, we can have dialog that I can understand. But do not come to me wrapped in the flag and say that you are true Americans.<br><br>
Too many died, too many suffered because you and individuals like S P A T Z contributed to the shame and ripped the hearts out of those that honorably served their country. Those who died fighting communist gooks in the jungles of South Vietnam. <br><br>
Today, even those that received this nations highest HONOR have never been properly recognized, honored or given the glory they so righteously deserve. <br>
Why? because of people like you, who ran then blamed those that served.<br><br>
Sorry, if you think its personal, it's personal only in as much as you contributed to the decline and the fall of the American dream. You and individuals like you brought shame and disgrace to our country then turned around and blamed honorable men that did serve. You're still doing it today. <br><br>
But compared to what I should say, all that I've fired at you above are but blanks compared to what those who died would say to you and others who disgraced our country's standing during that time and era. <br><br>
One day perhaps I will put into words what is in my heart and was in the hearts of those who served and those who died. Those words are yet, to be said. That underserved shame laid upon them still needs to be discarded. Someday those words must and will be said.<br>
 <br>
What is ironic is that I find those words in your postings, in between the lines of what you say and try to justify. They are words that beg to be said, they are and have been silently tearing at your heart all these years with shame and guilt. As I have said to S P A T Z, and now to you, YOU can no longer justify in your heart what your mind told you long ago was wrong.<br><br>

